# Robot Garage — `git remote origin`

When the workspace is **robot-garage** (path or repo folder name includes `robot-garage`, or work is clearly for that GitHub project), ensure `origin` is correct **before** `git push`, opening PRs, or recommending remotes.

**Canonical URL:** `https://github.com/moh-obaida/robot-garage.git`

## Check and fix (repo root)

1. Run `git remote -v` (or infer from context).
2. If there is no `origin`:
   ```bash
   git remote add origin https://github.com/moh-obaida/robot-garage.git
   ```
3. If `origin` exists but the URL is not the canonical one above:
   ```bash
   git remote set-url origin https://github.com/moh-obaida/robot-garage.git
   ```
4. Confirm with `git remote -v`.

Only change remotes for this project context; do not force-push or rewrite history unless the user explicitly requests it.
